doc.field: Open 365 days a year, Bok Tower Gardens, is a "must see" gem. Surrounded by rolling hills of orange groves this National Historic Landmark will warm your heart with it's beautiful Olmsted gardens, the 205-foot art deco Singing Tower, and the enchanting Mediterranean Pinewood Estate. Dedicated is 1929 as a gift from Dutch immigrant Edward Bok, a Pulitzer Prize-winning author and world peace advocate, this attraction sits between Tampa and Orlando. (PhotoJulie Fletcher)
